content:
The Integration Procedure Action runs a subordinate Integration Procedure. To specify that the subordinate Integration Procedure runs asynchronously, select Remote Options and enter useFuture: true as its value. When you run the Integration Procedure, you can see the future call in the debug log. The Additional Input property allows data to be passed in as key/value pairs.

Integration Procedure Action Properties are unique or function uniquely in this context. The Workflow for Integration Procedure Action Example shows a Parent and child Integration Procedures transform a list of paired values into a list of keys and values.

You can pass data as key/value pairs using the Additional Input property.
Remote Options allow you to specify that a subordinate Integration Procedure runs asynchronously, with useFuture: true as its value.
The Integration Procedure Action Properties are unique or function uniquely in this context.
title: Integration Procedure Actions in OmniStudio
